# GurbaniLens cloud ASR API keys.
#
# Copy this file to `.env` at the repo root and populate the keys you
# have access to. Keys are injected into the iOS app's Info.plist at
# build time by `scripts/inject_env_to_plist.sh` (wired as a
# postBuildScript in ios/GurbaniLens/project.yml).
#
# `.env` is in .gitignore — do not commit real keys.
#
# Both keys are optional. A missing key disables that cloud provider;
# the Settings → Voice recognition → Cloud picker will still let you
# pick the provider, but starting it will throw "missing key" and the
# user can fall back to WhisperKit (the local default).
#
# Long-term we'll proxy these through Taaj backend (api.taajsingh.com)
# so the keys never ship to user devices. v1 is direct-to-provider for
# the Compare-mode A/B test only.

# Sarvam Saaras-v3 streaming ASR (Indian language SOTA, ₹30/hour).
# Get a key at https://www.sarvam.ai → Console.
SARVAM_API_KEY=

# Google Gemini 2.5 Flash (multimodal, ~5× cheaper than Sarvam).
# Get a key at https://ai.google.dev → Get API key (Generative Language API).
GEMINI_API_KEY=
